data.name: Chespin
data.flavorText: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

data.name: Fennekin
data.flavorText: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Froakie
data.flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

data.name: Sylveon
data.flavorText: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

data.name: Xerneas
data.flavorText: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

data.name: Yveltal
data.flavorText: When this legendary Pokémon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of all living creatures.

data.name: Dragalge
data.flavorText: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

data.name: Skiddo
data.flavorText: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

data.name: Honedge
data.flavorText: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

data.name: Machamp
data.flavorText: Its four ruggedly developed arms can launch a flurry of 1,000 punches in just two seconds.

data.name: Trevenant
data.flavorText: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

data.name: Slurpuff
data.flavorText: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

data.name: Gogoat
data.flavorText: It can tell how its trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathetic sense lets them run as if one being.

data.name: Bronzong
data.flavorText: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

data.name: Darkrai
data.flavorText: It chases people and Pokémon from its territory by causing them to experience deep, nightmarish slumbers.

data.name: Shiftry
data.flavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

data.name: Greninja
data.flavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

data.name: Pyroar
data.flavorText: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

data.name: Xerneas
data.flavorText: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

data.name: Yveltal
data.flavorText: When this legendary Pokémon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

data.name: Treecko
data.flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

data.name: Torchic
data.flavorText: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Mudkip
data.flavorText: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

data.name: Kingdra
data.flavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life-forms can survive.

data.name: Ditto
data.flavorText: It has the ability to reconstitute its entire cellular structure to transform into whatever it sees.

data.name: Altaria
data.flavorText: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.

data.name: Heliolisk
data.flavorText: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

data.name: Meowstic
data.flavorText: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

data.name: Regirock
data.flavorText: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.

data.name: Pangoro
data.flavorText: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won't put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

data.name: Kyogre
data.flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

data.name: Groudon
data.flavorText: This legendary Pokémon is said to represent the land. It went to sleep after dueling Kyogre.

data.name: Blissey
data.flavorText: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

data.name: Fearow
data.flavorText: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

data.name: Malamar
data.flavorText: It lures its prey close with hypnotic motions, then wraps its tentacles around it before finishing it off with digestive fluids.

data.name: Salamence
data.flavorText: It's uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.

data.name: Gyarados
data.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

data.name: Rayquaza
data.flavorText: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

data.name: Latios
data.flavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

data.name: Jirachi
data.flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

data.name: Jirachi
data.flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

data.name: Chesnaught
data.flavorText: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

data.name: Reshiram
data.flavorText: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

data.name: Palkia
data.flavorText: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

data.name: Zekrom
data.flavorText: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

data.name: Dialga
data.flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

data.name: Latias
data.flavorText: It can telepathically communicate with people. It changes its appearance using its down that refracts light.

data.name: Latios
data.flavorText: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokémon that dislikes fighting.

data.name: Black Kyurem
data.flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

data.name: White Kyurem
data.flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

data.name: Regigigas
data.flavorText: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

data.name: Arceus
data.flavorText: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

data.name: Chespin
data.flavorText: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

data.name: Hoopa
data.flavorText: It gathers things it likes and pushes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

data.name: Sableye
data.flavorText: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

data.name: Celebi
data.flavorText: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

data.name: Trevenant
data.flavorText: Using its roots as a nervous system, it controls the trees in the forest. It's kind to the Pokémon that reside in its body.

data.name: Pikachu
data.flavorText: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

data.name: Umbreon
data.flavorText: When exposed to the moon's aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it's filled with a mysterious power.

data.name: Mewtwo
data.flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

data.name: Mewtwo
data.flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

data.name: Gyarados
data.flavorText: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

data.name: Mew
data.flavorText: Its DNA is said to contain the genetic codes of all Pokémon, so it can use all kinds of techniques.

data.name: Celebi
data.flavorText: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

data.name: Jirachi
data.flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

data.name: Manaphy
data.flavorText: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

data.name: Darkrai
data.flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

data.name: Shaymin
data.flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude and the message it delivers.

data.name: Arceus
data.flavorText: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

data.name: Victini
data.flavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.

data.name: Keldeo
data.flavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are too fast to follow.

data.name: Genesect
data.flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

data.name: Meloetta
data.flavorText: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

data.name: Moltres
data.flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

data.name: White Kyurem
data.flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body becomes frozen when the energy leaked out.

data.name: Zygarde
data.flavorText: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.

data.name: Tyranitar
data.flavorText: If it rampages, it knocks down mountains and buries rivers. Maps must be redrawn afterward.

data.name: Pansear
data.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves with volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Gastly
data.flavorText: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

data.name: Vivillon
data.flavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

data.name: Froakie
data.flavorText: It protects its skin by covering its body in delicate bubbles. Beneath its happy-go-lucky air, it keeps a watchful eye on its surroundings.

data.name: Floette
data.flavorText: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

data.name: Lucario
data.flavorText: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

data.name: Rayquaza
data.flavorText: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

data.name: Azelf
data.flavorText: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

data.name: Magikarp
data.flavorText: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

data.name: Yanmega
data.flavorText: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

data.name: Volcanion
data.flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

data.name: Clawitzer
data.flavorText: By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.

data.name: Hoopa
data.flavorText: It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.

data.name: Zygarde
data.flavorText: It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives.

data.name: Ho-Oh
data.flavorText: It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted Trainer by shining its bright, rainbow-colored wings.

data.name: Lugia
data.flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

data.name: Black Kyurem
data.flavorText: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

data.name: Braixen
data.flavorText: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.

data.name: Greninja
data.flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

data.name: Weezing
data.flavorText: Very rarely, a sudden mutation can result in two small Koffing twins becoming conjoined as a Weezing.

data.name: Volcanion
data.flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

data.name: Magearna
data.flavorText: Magearna, with its metallic body, is an artificial Pokémon created 500 years ago by humans.

data.name: Absol
data.flavorText: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.

data.name: Snorlax
data.flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

data.name: Giratina
data.flavorText: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
